		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Armor for bards<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Armor for bards";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 6th 2:42 AM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=104693455215026&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=104693455215026&num=3&post=1&replyto=104693455215026"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=104693455215026></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=205284"><span id=>calabreso</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />4 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=calabreso&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'm looking to start a bard (half elf). I was wondering what stats were key to bards. When buying armor what should i focus on? AC? Dex? CHa? Str? Which are important and which are more important than others? This is definetely a twink, so i got tons of money to spare. Thanks.<br><br>Qtee &lt;Midnight&gt;<br>First Bard<br>Solusek Ro Server<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >3 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 6th 8:13 AM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=104693455215026&num=3&post=1&replyto=104695438516088"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=104695438516088></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61546"><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1262 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.57]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Some folks say all into STA to maximize HP during the high end game.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you go on raids (or plan to a lot) then maybe that is a good idea.  If you plan to solo mostly then kiting does not require as many HP.  But STA is the hardest stat to raise with gear.<br><br>DEX is important since it helps prevent 'missed notes' - the bard equivelent of a spell fizzle.<br><br>CHA is needed to help with charming and mezzing targets. It also reduces the chance a target will aggro on you after a failed lull.<br><br>STR is good since bards do wear plate armor.  It can get heavy.  As a bard you are not a primary melee class. Your job is not based soley on how much weapon damage you do.<br><br>AC is nice since bard songs draw aggro to the bard much like heal spells draw aggro to a cleric/druid/shaman.  <br><br>In my case I put the most points into DEX and CHA with a touch into STR.  I started out with FS plate armor and now use RyGor.  Its been quite adequate.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
